        <h2>Short Description</h2>
        <p>Maldeth is the middle of the United Federation of Earth colonies, and is technically under the tutalige of the <a href="uft">United Federation of Utopia</a> in order to provide an equal level of support.</p>
        <p>Following the betrayal of Jugendfuhrer Jason Hellsbeck, he fled to Maldeth, where  the local lords and Kinderfuhrer Dynvis kept him safe until a friendly lord in what was left of the <a href="vers">Vers Empire</a> was able to take him in.</p>
        <p>Because of this, Maldeth has always been seen as a bit of a rebel within the Federation. Breaking the tradiation of the people being above the lords, the Maldethian Senate's "Representative Act" was seen as a damning piece of legislation for those who valued a fair and equal democracy for all. Instead requiring that anyone who wishes to hold office also hold an amount of land equal to the scale of the office they wish to take.</p>
        <p>For now, the Colony is holding on by a thread, no one is sure what will happen when the Kinderfuhrer leaves office, as no one has the land required to take the office.</p>
        <h2>History</h2>
        <p>Maldeth was first colonized following the second imperial war. While initally not as prosperous as the other colonies, when the <a href="rhineland">Rhineland Galaxy</a> was destroyed, the remaining world ships that had not yet left the mily way, or were still under production were rerouted towards the dominions of the Federation.</p>
        <p>During this period of booming colonization, Maldeth went from being seen as equal to a dwarf galaxy to actually being a nation itself. The population boom was mostly in the form of those who were looking for whatever work they could get their hands on, this was especially true for the large grops of <a href="germushia">Germishian</a> refugese.</p>
        <p>The colonists were quick to maintain their roots, the Germishians began to restore standard Versiarian ideals into the government, slowly creating a state that depended more and more on the aritocicy.</p>
        <p>Following Fuhrer Goodwins reforms Maldeth took their new found independence to the extreme, passing the "Representative Act" among numerous other measures to consolidate power among the lords. In stark opposition to the <a href="ufu">United Federation of Utopia</a> who embraced the more democractic principles. But for that same reason, Earth can't legislate against it.</p>
        <h2>Government</h2>
        <p>Like other Federation Dominions, Maldeth offically has two major houses of government, the House of the Lords and the House of the People, composed of two and three subhouses respectively.</p>
        <p>Maldeth, Unlike other Dominions, has a stronger House of the Lords, especially the lower house. While in the House of the People, only the Senate holds any real power at this point.</p>
        <br>
