                        <li>House of Commons - For the everyday people, normally the most powerful house, unfornately due to poorly written laws and a willfully ignorant people, the ability to legislate over citizens has been given to the lower house of lords, making the House of Commons effecitvely useless.</li>
                        <li>The Senate - For the government, still has the ability to overule actions of the houes of Commons and Representatives for now.</li>
                    </ol>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </p>
        <h2>Army</h2>
        <p>The army of Maldeth federally is weak. Like many Versarian nations Maldeths lords hold a very strong military power. In terms of armies, almost no planet execpt for those with vital federal functions have federal troops, and the standing army is disproportionately smaller then the other colonies. Otherwise it is structured the same as the United Federation of Earth.</p>
        <h2>Navy</h2>
        <p>The Federal navy of Maldeth is in a simliar state to that of the army. Very weak and poorly maintained. Unlike most other colonies that have been buying the old military surplus weapons during the rearmerment, Maldeth instead chose to delay a naval retrofit for another three centuries EST. The bold assumption of Kinderfuhrer Dynvis that war will not come, and if it does, it should not involve Maldeth is spoken about with hushed whispers in the halls of Parlimeant on Earth.</p>
